<subSubSection id="F6672CF04D3725E07BB0C6670540EBDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="68EFE7BF3A9436892837F72B3937BCD3" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9DDCB15A906111F206D65F403D3C2E9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Macau specimens exhibit a total length of 6.0-6.5 mm and a maximum width of 2.0-2.5 mm. The species is nocturnal and attracted to artificial lights. In the past, it has been misidentified and confused with 
<taxonomicName id="3F0D8F29E1080AC4FCA39D5B175D999E" genus="R." lsidName="R. honesta" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="honesta">
<emphasis id="DA22427E979946603B370FF666E94A06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">R. honesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="15119B1B80BF545DFFC579B40A68C038" author="Hua, L-Z" journalOrPublisher="List of Chinese Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 612" refId="B68" refString="Hua, L-Z, 2002. List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou. List of Chinese Insects 2: 1 - 612" title="List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou." volume="2" year="2002">Hua 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C8B37F3FD246D503C15906A4E5AE2703" author="Chou, W-I" journalOrPublisher="Owl Publishing House, Taipei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B21" refString="Chou, W-I, 2004. The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae. Owl Publishing House, Taipei" title="The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae." year="2004">Chou 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3D5322A38640C6DADB9A132D778B037E" author="Chou, W-I" journalOrPublisher="Owl Publishing House, Taipei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B22" refString="Chou, W-I, 2008. The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae (second edition). Owl Publishing House, Taipei" title="The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae (second edition)." year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6696E6C7317230E56A4036E01EAC8D93" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
), with consequent mix up of their respective distribution records (
<bibRefCitation id="1562CA51DD0A531824806806A6DE1929" author="Hua, L-Z" journalOrPublisher="List of Chinese Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 612" refId="B68" refString="Hua, L-Z, 2002. List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou. List of Chinese Insects 2: 1 - 612" title="List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou." volume="2" year="2002">Hua 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6A7E7869F4437D1D48E86581366F1249" author="Lin, M-Y" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B89" refString="Lin, M-Y, Yang, X-K, 2019. Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae." year="2019">Lin and Yang 2019</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="D005537CA860E731D2099C744E4BEA00" author="Gressitt, JL" journalOrPublisher="Longicornia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 667" refId="B56" refString="Gressitt, JL, 1951. Longicorn beetles of China. Longicornia 2: 1 - 667" title="Longicorn beetles of China." volume="2" year="1951">Gressitt (1951)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="147B8F547C71A5FC4863D10F4635713F" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Cucumis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cucumis sativus" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sativus">
<emphasis id="7CB5F604C16F80CAD628C51597662960" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cucumis sativus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is among its host plants and in Hong Kong larvae have been found boring into stems of 
<taxonomicName id="F937E28C60D9B0E57C23C6B24EC96A95" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Cucumis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cucumis melo" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="melo">
<emphasis id="930FA82CA1392FC313EC26B274BA5546" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cucumis melo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="35388053BEABE1A9A2792EFEB06C6FBA" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
